result.execSummary:
The defendant Kyle Edwin Gille was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Kyle Edwin Gille is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Kyle Edwin Gille was found guilty of Possession of Cocaine/Coca, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called at 3:06 PM.  Defendant Kyle Edwin Gille in court with attorney Fitch J. Taylor.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Taylor informs the Court of a Global Resolution.  Defendant changes his plea from Not Guilty to No Contest.  Attorney Taylor files Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form with the Court.  Court questions Defendant regarding Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form and his plea change.  Court questions Attorney Taylor regarding Defendant's plea change and Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form.  Defendant understands penalties, etc.  Court is satisfied Defendant enter his plea knowingly, freely, volunarily, and intelligently with the Court and will adjudicate him Guilty based on his No Contest plea.  State requesting amending count 1 to 964.41(3g)(c), 75 day jail sentence in the Lafayette County Jail with Huber Privileges, costs, 60 DTP, and civil judgment, dismissing count 2.  Attorney Taylor makes a statement to the Court.  Court does order.
Status conference on April 4, 2017 at 01:30 pm.
Status conference on March 21, 2017 at 01:30 pm.
